Last time I checked about three months ago Shadowbane had a freeze issue with four or more mages casting at the same time. I am not sure if they fixed it or not. 

Gods Wrath Clan has SB and SWG back on their forum since both are being played via internet soon.

Both games rely on “clan” numbers for the simple fact that you will have to rely upon other players to get supplies. Since the number of characters that can be created is one per server on SWG. The only other way to add another character for your fighting force is to buy another account. This makes it important to gather up people you can trust with different special skills. It is possible to get special weapons from other factions with SWG if you have the smuggling skill. If different factions can trade without killing each other at a neutral zone then this should not be a huge problem.  For example if no one in your clan has a designer to make your next weapon then the constructor has to look around for one which might take a long time. 

